  "time_ut": 1660935375,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u2019\u0bae\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb3 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0baf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b92\u0bb0\u0bc1 \u0baa\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd\u2019",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "'Part of Mattala Airport to be sold'",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Even now the airport is facing a deficit of USD 100 million due to non-regular flights arriving at Mattala airport.",
        "Therefore, a portion of the airport office should be sold, said Minister for Docks and Civil Aviation Nimal Siripaladi Silva.",
        "Mattala Airport is still facing a USD 100 million deficit. Due to Covid threats and other factors, flights are not being landed there. However, we are trying to convert it into a revenue generating airport.",
        "Therefore, we should create a program by getting various concessions for the flights there and present recommendations to the airlines of those countries to all the countries of the world. We also believe that it will be successful.",
        "We have taken hundred million dollar loans to renovate this airport. Therefore steps should be taken to rehabilitate Mattalai Airport. Especially to be privatized. He said it does not mean selling the entire airport, but a part of it."
      ],
